This paper discusses the use of cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). It also involves the use of channel state information (CSI) to improve network performance, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The proposed policy also involves adapting to the fading channel conditions, which could be considered a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiuser diversity to improve network throughput, which could be classified as a control systems approach (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of transmission rates, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
